library(tidyverse)
library(gt)
library(GPfit)
library(BASS)
f <- function(x1,x2) {
  return((6 * x1 - 2)^2 * sin(12 * x2 - 4))
}
# seed with a few evaluations:
n0 <- 8
evaluations <- matrix(
  as.numeric(NA),
  ncol = 3, nrow = n0,
  dimnames = list(NULL, c("x1", "x2", "y"))
)
evaluations[, "x1"] <- seq(0, 1, length.out = n0)
evaluations[, "x2"] <- seq(0, 1, length.out = n0)
evaluations[, "y"] <- f(evaluations[, "x1"],evaluations[, "x2"]) 
evaluations %>%
  as_tibble

Iterative run

max_iterations = 15

for (iteration in 1:max_iterations) {

fit <- bass(
  xx = evaluations[, 1:2],
  y = evaluations[, "y"],
  degree = 2,
  verbose = F
)


x_new <- data.frame(seq(0,1, length.out = 1000),seq(0,1, length.out = 1000))
pred <- predict(fit, newdata = data.frame(x = x_new))
mu <- pred[1000,]
X <- evaluations[, 1:2]

mesh <- data.frame(seq(0,1, length.out = 1000),seq(0,1, length.out = 1000))

y  <- NULL;
for (elem in 1:length(X)){
  tmp <- abs(mesh - X[elem])
  y <- rbind(y, tmp)
}
finals <- y |> apply(2,min)
sigma <- finals * 3


kappa <- 20 # tunable
lower_confidence_bound <- mu - kappa * sigma

minimo <- x_new[which.min(lower_confidence_bound),which.min(lower_confidence_bound)]

evaluations <- rbind(evaluations, c(minimo,minimo, f(minimo,minimo)))
}

Plot

plot_posterior <- function() {
  plot(
    x_new, mu,
    type = "l", col = "blue", lwd = 2, lty = "dotted",
    ylim = c(-10, 20),
    xlab = "x", ylab = "f(x)", main = "Posterior of f"
  )
  polygon(
    c(x_new, rev(x_new)),
    c(mu + sigma, rev(mu - sigma)),
    col = rgb(0, 0, 1, 0.25), border = NA
  )
  points(evaluations, pch = 16)
  legend(
    "topleft",
    c(expression(f[n[0]]), expression(mu(x)), expression(mu(x) %+-% sigma(x))),
    col = c("black", "blue", "blue"), pch = c(16, NA, NA),
    lty = c(NA, "dotted", NA), lwd = c(NA, 2, 1), bty = "n",
    fill = c(NA, NA, rgb(0, 0, 1, 0.25)),
    border = c(NA, NA, NA), ncol = 3, text.width = 0.1
  )
}
par(cex = 1.1, mfrow = c(1, 1), mar = c(5.1, 4.1, 4.1, 2.1))
plot_posterior()

par(cex = 1.1, mfrow = c(1, 2))
plot(
  x_new, lower_confidence_bound,
  type = "l", col = "red",
  xlab = "x", ylab = expression("a"["LCB"]),
  main = "GP lower confidence bound"
)
plot_posterior()
